# --- CircuitPython Specifics ---
# 'boot.out' is generated by the Pico every time it restarts.
# If you track this, you will have merge conflicts on every single commit.
boot.out

# 'settings.toml' contains WiFi SSID and Passwords.
# NEVER commit this. It is a security risk.
settings.toml

# --- Python Generated Files ---
# These are compiled python files that your computer makes.
# They are useless to other people and cause clutter.
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# --- OS System Files ---
# Mac and Windows junk files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
._*

# --- Editor / IDE Settings ---
# You generally don't want to force your VS Code settings on your team
.vscode/
.idea/

# --- Optional: Libraries ---
# Standard practice is to ignore 'lib/', but for a Student Team Project,
# I actually RECOMMEND putting a # in front of this (commenting it out).
# That way, if you add the 'neopixel' library, your teammates get it automatically.
# lib/
